[
    {
        "content": "<p>I believe Core Lean has improved the possibility of omitting section variables a lot, but a PhD student in Bonn - <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"651332\">@Sven Manthe</span> - noticed one place where the current behavior isn't ideal yet.</p>\n<p>Consider the following code:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Algebra</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Group</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">Basic</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Group</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">-- stuff about groups</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">CommGroup</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">omit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Group</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">lemma</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- error</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>This errors, because Lean uses the <code>[Group G]</code> instance to interpret what <code>*</code> means, and then complains that it cannot omit that variable. Ideally, the <code>[Group G]</code> was never available to begin with, and type-class inference would just find the <code>[CommGroup G]</code> instance instead.<br>\n(Note: this is a pattern we might not want in Mathlib, that's a separate discussion)</p>",
        "id": 546698863,
        "sender_full_name": "Floris van Doorn",
        "timestamp": 1761230440
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Here is an artificial, Mathlib-free MWE:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">section</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Inhabited</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Classical</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">choice</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">infer_instance</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- works fine</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">Classical</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">choice</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">infer_instance</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">end</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Nonempty</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Inhabited</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">omit</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Nonempty</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Classical</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">choice</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">infer_instance</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">Classical</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">choice</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">G</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">infer_instance</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rfl</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">-- Result: error. Expected: behaves like theorem `foo`.</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
